Average theatre
May 2018 • Solo
This review is just about the place, not about the spectacle (incidentally, excellent).

The staff makes an effort to set up an atmosphere and to show themselves as some version of 'neo-cool'. Well tried.

We stop following the invitation when queues take place on the next pavement, queue management is performed by security managers, and when some 10 people can bypass the queue.

The room is badly set, with a few seats facing a wall rather than the scene. Sea comfort is average.
